qas.question: What is the highest ranking court in Ireland?
Ireland's highest court has the power to determine whether laws are allowed by what document?
Who is the highest judge in Ireland's Supreme Court?
Besides chief justice, how many other judges sit on Ireland's Supreme Court?
Where is Ireland's Supreme Court seated?
The lower courts are made of a Chief Justice and how many other judges?
What organization's advice does the Chief Justice take when appointing Supreme Court Judges?
Where does the appellate court sit in Dublin?

context: <a0_0>The Supreme Court<a0_0/> is the highest court in Ireland. It has authority to interpret <a1_0>the constitution<a1_0/>, and strike down laws and activities of the state that it finds to be unconstitutional. It is also the highest authority in the interpretation of the law. Constitutionally it must have authority to interpret the constitution but its further appellate jurisdiction from lower courts is defined by law. The Irish Supreme Court consists of its presiding member, <a2_0>the Chief Justice<a2_0/>, and <a3_0><b5_0>seven<b5_0/> other judges<a3_0/>. Judges of the Supreme Court are appointed by the President in accordance with the binding advice of <b6_0>the Government<b6_0/>. The Supreme Court sits in <a4_0>the <b7_0>Four Courts<b7_0/> in Dublin<a4_0/>.
